      "DepositRequest": {
        "properties": {
          "_embedded": {
            "description": "Embedded objects that are requested by the \`expand\` query parameter.",
            "properties": {
              "customer": {
                "type": "object",
              },
              "transactions": {
                "description": "Most recent associated transactions.",
                "maxItems": 10,
                "type": "array",
              },
              "website": {
                "type": "object",
              },
            },
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": "object",
          },
          "_links": {
            "description": "Related links.",
            "items": {
              "properties": {
                "href": {
                  "description": "Link URL.",
                  "type": "string",
                },
                "rel": {
                  "description": "Type of link.",
                  "enum": [
                    "self",
                    "deposit",
                    "transactions",
                  ],
                  "type": "string",
                },
              },
              "type": "object",
            },
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": "array",
          },
          "amounts": {
            "description": "List of available deposit amounts.

If \`amounts\` is not specified when a deposit is created, amounts are determined from the chosen strategy.
For more information, see the [\`strategyId\` property](https://www.rebilly.com/catalog/all/deposits/postdepositrequest/#!t=request&path=strategyId).",
            "items": {
              "format": "double",
              "minimum": 0.01,
              "type": "number",
            },
            "type": "array",
          },
          "createdTime": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CreatedTime",
          },
          "currency": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CurrencyCode",
          },
          "customAmount": {
            "description": "Custom amount restrictions.
If this value is \`null\`,  custom amounts are prohibited.
If \`customAmount\` is not specified when a deposit request is created, amount restrictions are determined from the chosen strategy.
For more information, see the [\`strategyId\` property](https://www.rebilly.com/catalog/all/deposits/postdepositrequest/#!t=request&path=strategyId).",
            "properties": {
              "maximum": {
                "description": "Maximum custom amount. This value must be equal to \`minimum\` + X * \`multipleOf\`, where X is any positive integer.",
                "format": "double",
                "minimum": 0.01,
                "type": "number",
              },
              "minimum": {
                "description": "Minimum custom amount.",
                "format": "double",
                "minimum": 0.01,
                "type": "number",
              },
              "multipleOf": {
                "description": "Multiple by which the custom amount increases.

For example, if \`minimum\` is equal to 5.30, and \`multipleOf\` is 0.50, the valid custom amount is 5.30, 5.80, 6.30, 6.80 and so on until the \`maximum\` value is reached.

A valid custom amount must be equal to \`minimum\` + X * \`multipleOf\`, where X is any non negative integer.",
                "format": "double",
                "minimum": 0.01,
                "type": "number",
              },
            },
            "required": [
              "minimum",
              "multipleOf",
              "maximum",
            ],
            "type": [
              "object",
              "null",
            ],
          },
          "customFields": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ResourceCustomFields",
            "description": "Custom fields related to the deposit request.
Custom field values are copied to created transactions if matching custom fields (name, type) exist.",
          },
          "customerId": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CustomerId",
          },
          "expirationTime": {
            "description": "Date and time at which the deposit request expires. The default expiration time is one hour from the time the request is created.",
            "format": "date-time",
            "type": "string",
          },
          "id": {
            "description": "ID of the deposit request.",
            "example": "dep_req_0YVJ65BSGYC3EAT58SEX8KY6J7",
            "maxLength": 50,
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": "string",
          },
          "notificationUrl": {
            "description": "URL where a server-to-server POST notification is sent.
This notification is sent when the transaction result is finalized after a timeout or an offsite interaction.

Do not interpret this notification as a confirmation,
complete a \`GET\` request to confirm the result of the transaction.
To ensure the request is not reattempted,
when the result is confirmed, respond with a \`2xx\` HTTP status code.

The following placeholders are available to use in this URI: \`{id}\` and \`{result}\`.
These placeholders are replaced the with the transaction ID and result accordingly.",
            "format": "uri",
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null",
            ],
          },
          "properties": {
            "additionalProperties": {
              "type": "string",
            },
            "description": "Properties that are available for the user to complete when they use the hosted deposit form.
Use this object to describe fields that are rendered and completed on the hosted deposit form.",
            "example": {
              "email": "email@example.com",
              "max": "33",
            },
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": [
              "object",
              "null",
            ],
          },
          "propertiesSchema": {
            "description": "Defines properties the user can complete when they use the hosted deposit form.
This field accepts [JSON-schema](https://json-schema.org/) drafts 4, 6, and 7.",
            "example": {
              "properties": {
                "email": {
                  "type": "string",
                },
                "max": {
                  "exclusiveMaximum": 100,
                  "minimum": 0,
                  "type": "integer",
                },
              },
              "required": [
                "email",
              ],
              "type": "object",
            },
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": [
              "object",
              "null",
            ],
          },
          "redirectUrl": {
            "description": "URL to redirect the customer to when a deposit is completed. The default value is the website URL.",
            "format": "uri",
            "type": "string",
          },
          "status": {
            "description": "Status of the request.",
            "enum": [
              "created",
              "pending",
              "initiated",
              "attempted",
              "completed",
              "expired",
            ],
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": "string",
            "x-enumDescriptions": {
              "attempted": "A funds deposit transaction was attempted and declined. This is a temporary state.",
              "completed": "A funds deposit transaction has been approved and completed. This is a permanent state.",
              "created": "Request is created, but it has not been visited by a customer. This is a temporary state.",
              "expired": "Request expired without an approved deposit transaction. This is a permanent state.",
              "initiated": "A funds deposit transaction has been initiated. This is a temporary state.",
              "pending": "Request has been visited by a customer, but no funds have been deposited yet. This is a temporary state.",
            },
          },
          "transactionId": {
            "deprecated": true,
            "description": "ID of the transaction that is used in the deposit request.",
            "example": "txn_0YVDTQJ8YWDGQACV2N2N5SPWQ0",
            "maxLength": 50,
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null",
            ],
          },
          "transactionIds": {
            "description": "List of transaction IDs that are associated with the deposit request.
This list includes transactions that are created from the deposit request.
There is a maximum of one \`approved\` transaction in the list.",
            "items": {
              "maxLength": 50,
              "type": "string",
            },
            "type": "array",
          },
          "updatedTime": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UpdatedTime",
          },
          "websiteId": {
            "description": "Website ID of the deposit. This value specifies the website with which the deposit is associated.",
            "example": "web_0YV7DE4Z26DQSA1AC92FBJ7SEG",
            "maxLength": 50,
            "type": "string",
          },
        },
        "required": [
          "websiteId",
          "customerId",
          "currency",
        ],
        "type": "object",
      },
      "DepositStrategy": {
        "properties": {
          "_links": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/SelfLink",
          },
          "amounts": {
            "description": "Deposit strategy amounts configuration.",
            "properties": {
              "adjustBaseToLastDeposit": {
                "default": false,
                "description": "Specifies if the base amount must be adjusted based on the last deposit.
If this value is \`true\`, the \`baseAmount\` is changed to the last successful deposit amount made using [Create a deposit request](https://www.rebilly.com/catalog/all/deposits/postdepositrequest).

If the customer has no successful deposits, \`baseAmount\` is not adjusted.",
                "type": "boolean",
              },
              "baseAmount": {
                "description": "First amount that is displayed to customer.",
                "format": "double",
                "minimum": 0.01,
                "type": "number",
              },
              "calculator": {
                "description": "Deposit amounts calculator.
This field specifies if amounts are calculated using an absolute or percentage calculation.

Amounts are specified in \`baseAmount\`, and increments are specified in \`increments\`.

Example: \`baseAmount: 10\` and \`increments: [20, 50, 100]\`.

- If the calculator is set to \`absolute\`: the amounts displayed to the customer are \`[10, 30, 60, 110]\`.
- If the calculator is set to \`percent\`: the amounts displayed to the customer are \`[10, 12, 15, 20]\`.",
                "enum": [
                  "absolute",
                  "percent",
                ],
                "type": "string",
              },
              "increments": {
                "description": "List of incremental amounts that are displayed to customer.

For more information, see the [\`calculator\` property](https://www.rebilly.com/catalog/all/deposits/postdepositstrategy#!t=request&path=amounts/calculator).",
                "items": {
                  "format": "double",
                  "minimum": 0.01,
                  "type": "number",
                },
                "type": "array",
              },
            },
            "required": [
              "calculator",
              "baseAmount",
              "increments",
            ],
            "type": "object",
          },
          "createdTime": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CreatedTime",
          },
          "customAmount": {
            "description": "Custom amount restrictions.
If this value is \`null\`,  custom amounts are prohibited.
If \`customAmount\` is not specified when a deposit request is created, amount restrictions are determined from the chosen strategy.
For more information, see the [\`strategyId\` property](https://www.rebilly.com/catalog/all/deposits/postdepositrequest#!t=request&path=strategyId).",
            "properties": {
              "maximum": {
                "description": "Maximum custom amount. This value must be equal to \`minimum\` + X * \`multipleOf\`, where X is any positive integer.",
                "format": "double",
                "minimum": 0.01,
                "type": "number",
              },
              "minimum": {
                "description": "Minimum custom amount.",
                "format": "double",
                "minimum": 0.01,
                "type": "number",
              },
              "multipleOf": {
                "description": "Multiple by which the custom amount increases.

For example, if \`minimum\` is equal to 5.30, and \`multipleOf\` is 0.50, the valid custom amount is 5.30, 5.80, 6.30, 6.80 and so on until the \`maximum\` value is reached.

A valid custom amount must be equal to \`minimum\` + X * \`multipleOf\`, where X is any non negative integer.",
                "format": "double",
                "minimum": 0.01,
                "type": "number",
              },
            },
            "required": [
              "minimum",
              "multipleOf",
              "maximum",
            ],
            "type": [
              "object",
              "null",
            ],
          },
          "filter": {
            "default": "",
            "description": "Filter that uses deposit request properties to determine if a deposit strategy is applicable for the request.
If this field is empty, the strategy is applicable for any request.",
            "example": "depositRequest.currency:USD",
            "type": "string",
          },
          "id": {
            "description": "ID of the deposit strategy.",
            "example": "dep_str_0YVJ64MAHTDPA97H8S7R5MYR1M",
            "maxLength": 50,
            "readOnly": true,
            "type": "string",
          },
          "name": {
            "description": "Name of the strategy.",
            "type": "string",
          },
          "updatedTime": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UpdatedTime",
          },
        },
        "required": [
          "name",
          "amounts",
          "customAmount",
        ],
        "type": "object",
      },
      "DetailedProblem": {
        "allOf": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/BlankProblem",
